Add CSS for the DAG canvas nodes in Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/canvas-build.css.

The DAG view renders nodes as absolutely-positioned divs. They currently use .canvas-chain__ring classes for ring state (unresolved, decided-grounded, etc) which still work. But they need their own wrapper class for hover, selection, and transitions.

Add these rules after the existing .canvas-chain section (around line 700):

/* === DAG Canvas === */
.canvas-dag {
  position: relative;
  overflow: visible;
}

.canvas-dag-node {
  position: absolute;
  width: var(--canvas-node-size, 60px);
  height: var(--canvas-node-size, 60px);
  border-radius: 50%;
  cursor: pointer;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  transition: transform 180ms ease, box-shadow 180ms ease;
}

.canvas-dag-node:hover {
  transform: scale(1.08);
  z-index: 2;
}

.canvas-dag-node--selected {
  outline: 3px solid var(--canvas-accent, #6CB6FF);
  outline-offset: 3px;
  z-index: 3;
}

.canvas-dag-node--drag-over {
  outline: 2px dashed var(--canvas-accent, #6CB6FF);
  outline-offset: 4px;
}

.canvas-dag-node__label {
  position: absolute;
  top: calc(var(--canvas-node-size, 60px) + 8px);
  left: 50%;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
  white-space: nowrap;
  font-size: 11px;
  color: var(--canvas-fg-dim, #8b949e);
  pointer-events: none;
  max-width: 120px;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
}

.canvas-dag-append {
  position: absolute;
  width: 40px;
  height: 40px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  border: 1.5px dashed var(--canvas-muted, #484f58);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: border-color 180ms ease, transform 180ms ease;
}

.canvas-dag-append:hover {
  border-color: var(--canvas-accent, #6CB6FF);
  transform: scale(1.1);
}

.canvas-dag-append--drag-over {
  border-color: var(--canvas-accent, #6CB6FF);
  background: rgba(108, 182, 255, 0.08);
}

Do NOT modify any existing CSS. Only append new rules.

Update Code&DBs/Workflow/surfaces/app/src/canvas/CanvasEdges.tsx to render edge labels.

The OrbitEdge type has gateLabel?: string and gateFamily?: string fields. When an edge has a gateLabel, render it at the midpoint of the bezier curve.

In the CanvasEdgesProps interface, add: edges need their gateLabel. The OrbitEdge type already has it.

After each <path> element, if the edge has a gateLabel, add:

{edge.gateLabel && (() => {
  const mx = (x1 + x2) / 2;
  const my = (y1 + y2) / 2;
  const textLen = edge.gateLabel!.length * 6.5 + 12;
  return (
    <g key={`label-${edge.id}`}>
      <rect
        x={mx - textLen / 2}
        y={my - 10}
        width={textLen}
        height={20}
        rx={4}
        fill="var(--canvas-surface, #161b22)"
        stroke="var(--canvas-border, #30363d)"
        strokeWidth={1}
      />
      <text
        x={mx}
        y={my + 4}
        textAnchor="middle"
        fontSize={11}
        fill="var(--canvas-fg-dim, #8b949e)"
        style={{ pointerEvents: 'none' }}
      >
        {edge.gateLabel}
      </text>
    </g>
  );
})()}

Wrap both the path and the optional label group in a <g> fragment so they stay together.

